ft parenthesis x plus 28 right parenthesis equals one tenth left parenthesis x minus a right parenthesis squared left parenthesis x minus b right parenthesis squared left parenthesis x minus c right parenthesis\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>28</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, where <math alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi>\n</math>, <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math>, and <math alttext=\"c\"><mi>c</mi>\n</math> are constants, which of the following could be the value of <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
